Former Vice-President Atiku Abubakar has reacted to the death of three abducted Greenfield varsity students. The Nation reports three of the kidnapped students of Greenfield University, Kasarami Kaduna, were found dead. Kaduna Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, confirmed the development on Friday. Atiku, in a terse post on Friday, described the killing of the abducted students as heartbreaking. He asked States to be granted constitutional roles in securing their terrains. “Heartbreaking to learn of the killing of 3 of the abducted students of Greenfield University, Kaduna. “How long shall we continue to lose precious souls? May their families and friends be comforted. “It is time states are granted constitutional roles in the management of security,”Atiku said